Key Match Events: Bobby Miller gave up seven runs, including five in the first inning.
Miller served up a first-pitch, three-run homer to Mickey Moniak.
Miller gave up two more home runs: first to Niko Kavadas in the second inning, then to Taylor Ward in the fifth.
Pre-Game Insights: Dodgers continue to believe in Miller and Buehler's potential for the postseason.
Manager Dave Roberts emphasized the importance of performance over stuff.
Clayton Kershaw is nursing a bone spur on his left big toe and continues to play catch.
Post-Match Reflections: Bobby Miller expressed frustration but acknowledged the need to move on.
Dodgers' manager Dave Roberts stressed the importance of performance and building a case for potential postseason roles.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Yoshinobu Yamamoto set to make his first start since June 15 due to a strained rotator cuff.
Tyler Glasnow making progress in his recovery from elbow tendinitis and could begin throwing bullpen sessions this weekend.
